**Proposition 3**.: _Let \(\mathbf{X}\in\mathbb{R}^{n\times d}\) represents the original dataset. Let \(\mathbf{V}\in\mathbb{R}^{n\times m^{\prime}}\) be a random noise matrix with each element independently drawn from \(\text{V}_{i,j}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^{2})\). Let \(\mathbf{U}\in\mathbb{R}^{d\times m^{\prime}}\) be a deterministic matrix such that for any \(j\in[m]\)_

\[\mathbf{U}_{:,(j-1)k+1},\cdots,\mathbf{U}_{:,jk}\text{ are orthonormal}\]

_The privacy mechanism \(\mathcal{M}_{det}(\mathbf{X})\triangleq\mathbf{X}\mathbf{U}+\mathbf{V}\) satisfies_

\[\left(\frac{m\alpha}{2\sigma^{2}}+\frac{\ln(1/\delta)}{\alpha-1},\delta \right)-\text{DP}.\]

