\[\text{D}_{\alpha}(\mathcal{M}(\mathbf{X})||\mathcal{M}(\mathbf{X} ^{\prime})) =\frac{\alpha}{2}\mathrm{vec}(\mathbf{X}\mathbf{U}-\mathbf{X}^{ \prime}\mathbf{U})^{T}(\sigma^{2}\mathbf{I}_{nm^{\prime}})^{-1}\mathrm{vec}( \mathbf{X}\mathbf{U}-\mathbf{X}^{\prime}\mathbf{U})\] \[=\frac{\alpha}{2\sigma^{2}}\mathrm{vec}((\mathbf{X}-\mathbf{X}^{ \prime})\mathbf{U})^{T}\mathrm{vec}((\mathbf{X}-\mathbf{X}^{\prime})\mathbf{U})\] \[=\frac{\alpha}{2\sigma^{2}}\|(\mathbf{X}_{i,:}-\mathbf{X}^{\prime} _{i,:})\mathbf{U}\|_{2}^{2}.\]

Without loss of generality, we assume

\[\mathbf{X}_{i,:}-\mathbf{X}^{\prime}_{i,:}=[x,0,\cdots,0]\quad\text{with }|x|\leq 1.\]

Additionally, recall the assumption that for any \(j\in[m]\), \(\mathbf{U}_{:,(j-1)k+1},\cdots,\mathbf{U}_{:,jk}\) are orthonormal. Hence, \(U_{1,(j-1)k+1}^{2}+\cdots+U_{1,jk+1}^{2}\leq 1\), leading to

